From 44ae438de0038546802f540e06535a5b6b5e66cd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 03:39:38 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 31/32] soc: mediatek: mtk-mmsys: add MT6797 routes and resets

MT6797 has a distinct MMSYS mux layout. Add the 29 high-level routes
representable by the current DDP component model, including the internal
virtual OVL and PATH0 writes needed by the active Gemini path. SPLIT0 and
dual-DSI remain outside the model because no corresponding component ID
exists.

Also expose the two active-low software-reset banks at offsets 0x140 and
0x144 as 64 linear resets. The offsets, selector values, masks, and reset
width are recovered from the exact Gemian source and cross-checked against
its retained active display dump.

Signed-off-by: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
---
 drivers/soc/mediatek/mt6797-mmsys.h | 190 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 drivers/soc/mediatek/mtk-mmsys.c    |   5 +
 2 files changed, 195 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/soc/mediatek/mt6797-mmsys.h

diff --git a/drivers/soc/mediatek/mt6797-mmsys.h b/drivers/soc/mediatek/mt6797-mmsys.h
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..2673a1a03
